<abstract><t>Hybrid measurement is the combination of metrics derived from passive and active measurement to produce a measurement result.  This document discusses use cases for hybrid measurement using metrics defined within the IPPM framework, and discusses requirements for the definition of passive methodologies for selected IPPM metrics.</t></abstract>

